page.title: 01KENNY HILL
page.content: Approx. 5 miles north of Mildenhall approached by Fen Droves - ie. Sheltons Drove and Holywell Drove. Flat fen fields about 9 to 10 feet above ordinance datum. Poor sandy - gravelly top soil. Used mainly for rough grazing. Some of the fields bordered by narrow plantation of conifers. The areas is artificially drained by open ditches leading into Milenhall Fen Drainage Broads main open drains, which in turn lead to the boards pumping station situated on the bank of the river Lark. There are two agricultural dwellings in the area.
